rComments: Jen is a great teacher she's is very enthusiastic and relatable.  Her assingements can get a little boring but they're rather easy which sort of makes up for it. I highly recommend her!
An excellent professor, it was a pleasure to take her class.
She really cares about the success of her students!  I have registered for the Environemental Sociology class that she will  be teaching and I look forward to having her as my prof again!
Jen is the best prof I've ever had. The class was always interesting and informative.  She genuinely cares about us students and wants us to do well. I'll definitely take classes with her again.

I thought she taught the class on Canadian society amazingly well.  I can tell she's a new prof but she puts so much into her course material and lectures.  The amount of course work was revised to be a fair amount.  She has a great sense of humor. I hope UO gives her more classes - she deserves them.
Jen is so awesome! I loved having a class with her. She's really pleasant and the class atmosphere is really laid back. We almost had a full class every lecture!
